    preGame:
      "### üéôÔ∏è STEP RIGHT UP, SPORTS FANS! IT'S PLAYOFF TIME IN OSTERRA! üèüÔ∏è\n\nHello, you beautiful souls, you seekers of carnage, you lovers of the grand old game! This is Nok the Corrupter coming to you live from the most wonderfully dilapidated patch of swamp in the realm‚Äî**The Sinking Field**! We are kicking off the post-season with a Best of 3 clash that‚Äôll make your teeth rattle! The air is thick with noxious fumes, the mud is up to our knees, and the playoff atmosphere is absolutely electric‚Äîor maybe that‚Äôs just the swamp gas igniting! \n\nOur home team today, the pride of the pits, the **Ebon Gate Corruptors**, are looking to defend their turf! I tell ya, folks, I saw Amedeo Bari in the tunnel polishing his boots with pure bacon grease‚Äînow that‚Äôs a man who knows how to slide through a tackle! Olnek Vizzone is over there clapping his hands in prime numbers, looking focused, looking sharp, looking ready to break some ribs for the glory of the Gate! They‚Äôve got the grit, they‚Äôve got the smell, and they‚Äôve got my heart!\n\nBut don't count out the visitors! Traveling down from the mountain peaks, we have **The Confluence Captains**! They‚Äôre looking a bit high-and-mighty for a bunch of Guild-backed glory-seekers. I caught Ladew Evelina chugging a raw egg‚Äîshell and all!‚Äîwhile O'Conner Maighdlin is refusing to speak unless it rhymes! Can you believe the gall of these mountain-dwellers? They might have the fancy scimitars and the Guild‚Äôs gold, but can they survive the sinkholes of Ebon Gate? \n\nIt's a beautiful day for Trollball, folks! The stands are sagging, the mud is churning, and the Everwar ensures that even if a player loses a head, they‚Äôll be back for Game 2! Let‚Äôs get ready for some sanctioned slaughter! üèêüí•",
    postGame:
      "### üéôÔ∏è THE FINAL WHISTLE BLOWS ON A SWAMP-SOAKED SHAMBLES! üèüÔ∏è\n\nGreat shades of Orzalon, what a display of athletic brutality we‚Äôve witnessed here today! While my beloved **Ebon Gate Corruptors** didn't quite find the basket, the medical tents are absolutely overflowing, and isn't that the real victory? The Confluence Captains take Game 1 of this series with a staggering 6-0 victory, but they‚Äôll be picking mud and teeth out of their gear for a month! Let‚Äôs break down this wonderful mess!\n\nThings started fast and filthy in Center Field! Simsar Carrelli scooped up the head early, but the Captains‚Äô O'Conner Maighdlin decided he wasn‚Äôt there to play ball‚Äîhe was there to play butcher! With a hatchet in hand, he sent Amedeo Bari and Napoleon Anzovin to the infirmary before the game even had its legs! I haven‚Äôt seen such efficient work since Cyfnerth the Butcher last went grocery shopping!\n\nThe Captains didn't just fight; they moved the leather. Carnahan Laud, that dandelion-eating dynamo, took a shot from the Away Field and zipped it right through the goal for 2 points! My Corruptors tried to respond, but the mud was a cruel mistress today. Smith Syst and Bullion Iglesias were trading passes like they were at a fancy tea party held by Maple the Tree, but they couldn't find the end zone!\n\nBefore we could even catch our breath, O'Conner Maighdlin‚Äîstill rhyming, I assume‚Äîthrew a long-range beauty from Center Field! **BOOM!** Two more points for the mountain-dwellers! The Corruptors looked stuck in the muck, and Behl Berstine made them pay, charging into the end zone for a 1-point dunk that felt like a dagger to the soul. It was 5-0 before the halftime fumes even started to make the fans hallucinate!\n\nSpeaking of halftime, our players came back looking a bit woozy! Between the noxious fumes of the Sinking Field and whatever questionable spirits they‚Äôre swilling in the locker room, the second half was a masterclass in drunken violence! Smith Syst got absolutely leveled by Richia Pazit, and the sound of that impact was sweeter than any siren's song! \n\nBut my boys wouldn't go down without a fight! Napoleon Anzovin got his revenge, putting Vonni Geoff into the dirt, and Ellette Paz absolutely flattened Stephan Lisk! It was a regular meat-grinder out there! Even the Guild of the Black Sky‚Äôs own Brennen Farno would‚Äôve blushed at the amount of blood being spent‚Äîand we know how he feels about spending anything!\n\nThe injuries just kept piling up! Richia Pazit, Behl Berstine, and Deach Sharlene all found themselves on the wrong end of a weapon. It was a beautiful, chaotic symphony of groans and clashing steel! If only Sir Tanos could see this‚Äîhe‚Äôd probably try to stab me for enjoying it so much, the big lug!\n\nDespite the Corruptors' best efforts to turn the game into a wrestling match, the Captains found one more opening. Belding Chloe, who I suspect spent the morning rubbing her armor in armpit sweat for 'luck,' powered through the defense and dunked the final point of the match! 6-0, a clean sweep on the scoreboard, even if the players are anything but clean!\n\nI must say, I‚Äôm disappointed in the result, but thrilled by the carnage! My Corruptors showed heart, mostly by leaving bits of it on the field. Those Captains think they‚Äôre so smart with their 'literacy' and their 'scimitars,' but they‚Äôre going to need more than a rhyme to survive Game 2! \n\nThe series stands at 1-0 in favor of the **Confluence Captains**. If the Corruptors don't find their footing in the mud soon, they‚Äôll be heading to the loser‚Äôs bracket faster than a fey circus flees a Linaius rant! \n\nFinal Score: **The Confluence Captains 6, The Ebon Gate Corruptors 0**. \n\nStay tuned for more Tuesday Night Trollball! May your drinks be strong and your armor be reinforced! Nok the Corrupter, signing off! üèêüíÄüçª",
