    preGame:
      "Step right up, ladies and gentlemen, ghouls and ghosts! Welcome to the spectacular opening of the Osterra Playoffs! Nok the Corrupter here, coming to you live from the soggy, sinking Serpent's Pass! We've got a real humdinger today as the popular local favorites, the Zmeigorod Snessengers, host those wood-walking warriors, Oak & Onslaught! This is Game 1 of a Best of 3 series, folks, and the stakes are higher than a mountain giant on stilts! The loser gets booted to the loser's bracket, and nobody wants that kind of shame hanging over their head!\\n\\nThe atmosphere here is simply electric‚Äîor maybe that's just the lightning from the Sudden Downpour we're expecting! The fans are packed in like sardines, and let me tell you, the Zmeigorod faithful are out in force! You can barely hear yourself think over the roar of the crowd. The Snessengers are the darlings of the realm right now, while Oak & Onslaught are looking like the scrappy underdogs trying to spoil the party. Even Sir Randy and his fancy Warden scouts are watching from the sidelines, probably wondering if their 'fancy bows' could ever match the raw power of a Trollball to the teeth!\\n\\nBefore the whistle, I caught a glimpse of some truly professional pre-game preparation! Milt Casady was leading Oak & Onslaught in a synchronized chant that grew so loud it nearly triggered a Rockslide early! Meanwhile, on the home side, Evalyn Pierrepont was meticulously polishing his helmet with a live snail! You can't make this stuff up, folks! And Northway Orran was striking theatrical poses that would make even God King Artorias jealous! Grab your grog and hold onto your hats, because this is playoff Trollball!",
    postGame:
      "What a game! What a spectacle! What a glorious display of bone-crunching mayhem! The underdogs have bitten back, folks! Oak & Onslaught walk into the Serpent's Pass and snatch Game 1 right out of the Bog Queen's hands! The final score stands at 3 to 2 in favor of the Wardens' favorites, and the Zmeigorod crowd is stunned into a silence so deep you could hear a snail crawl across Evalyn Pierrepont‚Äôs helmet!\\n\\nThe action started fast and mean! Kleinstein MacGregor scooped up that leather head early in Center Field, looking like she was ready to make a name for herself. But Milt Casady had other plans! He swung that blackjack with the grace of a seasoned executioner, sending Kleinstein to the dirt and into the medical tent! It was a beautiful sight, truly!\\n\\nNot to be outdone, Hole Bowerman decided to join the fray! She lowered her lance and absolutely flattened Evalyn Pierrepont! The Snessengers were reeling early, their high popularity scores not doing a lick of good against the cold, hard wood of the Wardens' weaponry. Rose Kluge tried to get some momentum going with a pass, but it was as wild as a drunken pixie and hit the turf with a thud!\\n\\nThen came the breakthrough! Wynnie Faina, wearing his boots on the wrong feet for luck, showed us why he's a star! He snagged the ball, dodged the defense, and charged into the End Zone for a thunderous dunk! The away fans went wild, and Oak & Onslaught took the lead! But they weren't finished yet, oh no!\\n\\nNormi Glaudia decided he didn't feel like running all the way to the basket. From right there in Center Field, he wound up and launched a Shoot that sailed through the goal like a shooting star! Two points! Just like that, the score was 3 to zero, and the Snessengers looked like they were sinking faster than their own stadium!\\n\\nZmeigorod tried to rally, bless their hearts. Delija Dowling made a valiant run, and Gere Cordelie managed to land a spectacular Shoot from Home Field just after the halftime break to bring them back within striking distance! It was a 3 to 2 game and the tension was thick enough to cut with a Kriegsmesser!\\n\\nBut the defense from the Onslaught was just too brutal! Teria Ravo and Affra Yanaton were handing out injuries like they were participation trophies! They took turns knocking Northway Orran and Evalyn Pierrepont out of the game again! It‚Äôs a miracle anyone was left standing to play the ball!\\n\\nMillham Evangeline was a one-demon wrecking crew in the closing minutes! They tackled Alded Sanjay and Arni Griffith back-to-back, sending both Snessengers to the healer with bells ringing in their ears! Even when the Snessengers tried to shoot from distance, the altitude and the pressure got to them, with both Arni and Kleinstein missing wide!\\n\\nThe game ended in a frantic scramble in the Away Field with Dare Wynnie desperately clutching the ball, but time simply ran out! The Zmeigorod Snessengers fall at home, and now they face a must-win situation in Game 2 or they'll be headed straight to the loser's bracket!\\n\\nSo, take that, you 'heroes' of the Grove! Valos the Eternal might think she rules the swamp, but today, she just rules a patch of dirt where her team got stomped! Oak & Onslaught takes a 1-0 lead in this Best of 3! I‚Äôm Nok the Corrupter, and I can‚Äôt wait to see who loses a limb next week! Goodnight, Osterra!",
